snippet.textDisplay:
I honestly don't think this has much to do with Novak, but far more to do with the political optics of whether he stays or leaves.

He should've never even been able to board on the plane to enter Australia in the first place, but Australian officials really missed the ball on this one. 

If they kick him out, the government can tell the people that they don't have double standards, but incur the wrath of Serbia. If they keep him, they resolve a diplomatic conflict, but risk the ire of people who'll claim double standards.

In my opinion, they should come to some sort of agreement where he's isolated the entire time but allowed to partipate in the Australian Open, and then asked to leave once he's out of the tournament. 
They already let him in and can chalk this up to screw ups in the immigration process, but stick to their guns on how seriously they view Covid. It seems like it'll have the least blowback, but we'll have to see what they decide to do
